{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# **Modeling and Evaluation — Cluster Analysis**"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a02",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "* Fit and evaluate a cluster model to group similar AI job profiles.\n",
    "* Understand the profile for each cluster.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Inputs\n",
    "\n",
    "* `outputs/datasets/collection/ai_job_dataset1.csv`\n",
    "* Instructions on which variables to use for data cleaning and feature engineering are found in their respective notebooks.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Outputs\n",
    "\n",
    "* Cluster Pipeline\n",
    "* Train Set\n",
    "* Most important features to define a cluster plot\n",
    "* Clusters Profile Description\n",
    "* Cluster Silhouette"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a03",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["---"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a04",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Change working directory"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a05",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We need to change the working directory from its current folder to its parent folder.\n",
    "\n",
    "* We access the current directory with `os.getcwd()`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-a06",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "current_dir = os.getcwd()\n",
    "current_dir"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a07",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We want to make the parent of the parent of current directory the new current directory.\n",
    "\n",
    "* `os.path.dirname()` gets the parent directory\n",
    "* `os.chdir()` defines the new current directory"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-a08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "os.chdir(os.path.dirname(current_dir))\n",
    "print(\"You set a new current directory\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-a09",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Confirm the new current directory"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-a10",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "current_dir = os.getcwd()\n",
    "current_dir"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-b01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Load Data"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-b02",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We load the raw dataset and drop:\n",
    "* `job_id` — identifier, non-predictive\n",
    "* `job_title`, `required_skills`, `company_name` — high-cardinality text columns\n",
    "* `salary_usd`, `salary_currency`, `salary_local` — target variables (avoid leakage)\n",
    "* `company_location`, `employee_residence` — very high cardinality (100+ countries)\n",
    "* `posting_date`, `application_deadline` — date strings, not used for clustering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-b03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "df = (\n",
    "    pd.read_csv(\"outputs/datasets/collection/ai_job_dataset1.csv\")\n",
    "    .drop(['job_id', 'job_title', 'salary_usd', 'salary_currency', 'salary_local',\n",
    "           'company_location', 'employee_residence', 'required_skills',\n",
    "           'posting_date', 'application_deadline', 'company_name'], axis=1)\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(df.shape)\n",
    "df.head(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Cluster Pipeline with all data"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c02",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## ML Cluster Pipeline"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "# Feature Engineering\n",
    "from feature_engine.encoding import OrdinalEncoder\n",
    "from feature_engine.selection import SmartCorrelatedSelection\n",
    "\n",
    "# Feat Scaling\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "\n",
    "# PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "# ML algorithm\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def PipelineCluster():\n",
    "    pipeline_base = Pipeline([\n",
    "        (\"OrdinalCategoricalEncoder\", OrdinalEncoder(\n",
    "            encoding_method='arbitrary',\n",
    "            variables=['experience_level', 'employment_type', 'company_size',\n",
    "                       'education_required', 'industry'])),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"SmartCorrelatedSelection\", SmartCorrelatedSelection(\n",
    "            variables=None, method=\"spearman\",\n",
    "            threshold=0.6, selection_method=\"variance\")),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"scaler\", StandardScaler()),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"PCA\", PCA(n_components=8, random_state=0)),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"model\", KMeans(n_clusters=8, random_state=0)),\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    return pipeline_base\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "PipelineCluster()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c04",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Principal Component Analysis (PCA)"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipeline_cluster = PipelineCluster()\n",
    "pipeline_pca = Pipeline(pipeline_cluster.steps[:-2])\n",
    "df_pca = pipeline_pca.fit_transform(df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df_pca.shape, '\\n', type(df_pca))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Apply PCA separately to the scaled data"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c07",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "n_components = 8\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def pca_components_analysis(df_pca, n_components):\n",
    "    pca = PCA(n_components=n_components).fit(df_pca)\n",
    "    x_PCA = pca.transform(df_pca)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ComponentsList = [\"Component \" + str(number)\n",
    "                      for number in range(n_components)]\n",
    "    dfExplVarRatio = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "        data=np.round(100 * pca.explained_variance_ratio_, 3),\n",
    "        index=ComponentsList,\n",
    "        columns=['Explained Variance Ratio (%)'])\n",
    "\n",
    "    dfExplVarRatio['Accumulated Variance'] = dfExplVarRatio[\n",
    "        'Explained Variance Ratio (%)'].cumsum()\n",
    "\n",
    "    PercentageOfDataExplained = dfExplVarRatio[\n",
    "        'Explained Variance Ratio (%)'].sum()\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(\n",
    "        f\"* The {n_components} components explain \"\n",
    "        f\"{round(PercentageOfDataExplained, 2)}% of the data \\n\")\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(9, 6))\n",
    "    sns.lineplot(data=dfExplVarRatio, marker=\"o\")\n",
    "    plt.xticks(rotation=90)\n",
    "    plt.yticks(np.arange(0, 110, 10))\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "pca_components_analysis(df_pca=df_pca, n_components=n_components)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca_components_analysis(df_pca=df_pca, n_components=4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def PipelineCluster():\n",
    "    pipeline_base = Pipeline([\n",
    "        (\"OrdinalCategoricalEncoder\", OrdinalEncoder(\n",
    "            encoding_method='arbitrary',\n",
    "            variables=['experience_level', 'employment_type', 'company_size',\n",
    "                       'education_required', 'industry'])),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"SmartCorrelatedSelection\", SmartCorrelatedSelection(\n",
    "            variables=None, method=\"spearman\",\n",
    "            threshold=0.6, selection_method=\"variance\")),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"scaler\", StandardScaler()),\n",
    "\n",
    "        # we update n_components to 4\n",
    "        (\"PCA\", PCA(n_components=4, random_state=0)),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"model\", KMeans(n_clusters=8, random_state=0)),\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    return pipeline_base\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "PipelineCluster()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Elbow Method and Silhouette Score"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c11",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipeline_cluster = PipelineCluster()\n",
    "pipeline_analysis = Pipeline(pipeline_cluster.steps[:-1])\n",
    "df_analysis = pipeline_analysis.fit_transform(df)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(df_analysis.shape, '\\n', type(df_analysis))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from yellowbrick.cluster import KElbowVisualizer\n",
    "\n",
    "visualizer = KElbowVisualizer(KMeans(random_state=0), k=(1, 11))\n",
    "visualizer.fit(df_analysis)\n",
    "visualizer.show()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from yellowbrick.cluster import SilhouetteVisualizer\n",
    "\n",
    "n_cluster_start, n_cluster_stop = 2, 6\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"=== Average Silhouette Score for different number of clusters ===\")\n",
    "visualizer = KElbowVisualizer(\n",
    "    KMeans(random_state=0), k=(n_cluster_start, n_cluster_stop),\n",
    "    metric='silhouette')\n",
    "visualizer.fit(df_analysis)\n",
    "visualizer.show()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(\"\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for n_clusters in np.arange(start=n_cluster_start, stop=n_cluster_stop):\n",
    "    print(f\"=== Silhouette plot for {n_clusters} Clusters ===\")\n",
    "    visualizer = SilhouetteVisualizer(\n",
    "        estimator=KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, random_state=0),\n",
    "        colors='yellowbrick')\n",
    "    visualizer.fit(df_analysis)\n",
    "    visualizer.show()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    print(\"\\n\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c14",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def PipelineCluster():\n",
    "    pipeline_base = Pipeline([\n",
    "        (\"OrdinalCategoricalEncoder\", OrdinalEncoder(\n",
    "            encoding_method='arbitrary',\n",
    "            variables=['experience_level', 'employment_type', 'company_size',\n",
    "                       'education_required', 'industry'])),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"SmartCorrelatedSelection\", SmartCorrelatedSelection(\n",
    "            variables=None, method=\"spearman\",\n",
    "            threshold=0.6, selection_method=\"variance\")),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"scaler\", StandardScaler()),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"PCA\", PCA(n_components=4, random_state=0)),\n",
    "\n",
    "        # we update n_clusters to 3\n",
    "        (\"model\", KMeans(n_clusters=3, random_state=0)),\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    return pipeline_base\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "PipelineCluster()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c15",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Fit Cluster Pipeline"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c16",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Quick recap of our data for training cluster pipeline"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c17",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = df.copy()\n",
    "print(X.shape)\n",
    "X.head(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c18",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Fit Cluster pipeline"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c19",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipeline_cluster = PipelineCluster()\n",
    "pipeline_cluster.fit(X)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c20",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Add cluster predictions to dataset"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c21",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We add a column `Clusters` (with the cluster pipeline predictions) to the dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c22",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X['Clusters'] = pipeline_cluster['model'].labels_\n",
    "print(X.shape)\n",
    "X.head(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c23",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"* Clusters frequencies \\n{\n",
    "    X['Clusters'].value_counts(normalize=True).to_frame().round(2)} \\n\\n\")\n",
    "X['Clusters'].value_counts().sort_values().plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c24",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "sns.set_style(\"whitegrid\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "sns.scatterplot(\n",
    "    x=df_analysis[:, 0], y=df_analysis[:, 1],\n",
    "    hue=X['Clusters'], palette='Set1', alpha=0.6)\n",
    "plt.scatter(\n",
    "    x=pipeline_cluster['model'].cluster_centers_[:, 0],\n",
    "    y=pipeline_cluster['model'].cluster_centers_[:, 1],\n",
    "    marker=\"x\", s=169, linewidths=3, color=\"black\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"PCA Component 0\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"PCA Component 1\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"PCA Components colored by Clusters\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-c25",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We save the cluster predictions from this pipeline to use in the future."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-c26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cluster_predictions_with_all_variables = X['Clusters']\n",
    "cluster_predictions_with_all_variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Fit a classifier, where the target is cluster predictions and features are the remaining variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d02",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["We copy X to a DataFrame `df_clf`"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_clf = X.copy()\n",
    "print(df_clf.shape)\n",
    "df_clf.head(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d04",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Split Train and Test sets"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    df_clf.drop(['Clusters'], axis=1),\n",
    "    df_clf['Clusters'],\n",
    "    test_size=0.2,\n",
    "    random_state=0\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(X_train.shape, X_test.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Create classifier pipeline steps"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d07",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Feat Selection\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectFromModel\n",
    "\n",
    "# ML algorithm\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def PipelineClf2ExplainClusters():\n",
    "    pipeline_base = Pipeline([\n",
    "        (\"OrdinalCategoricalEncoder\", OrdinalEncoder(\n",
    "            encoding_method='arbitrary',\n",
    "            variables=['experience_level', 'employment_type', 'company_size',\n",
    "                       'education_required', 'industry'])),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"SmartCorrelatedSelection\", SmartCorrelatedSelection(\n",
    "            variables=None, method=\"spearman\",\n",
    "            threshold=0.6, selection_method=\"variance\")),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"scaler\", StandardScaler()),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"feat_selection\", SelectFromModel(\n",
    "            GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=0))),\n",
    "\n",
    "        (\"model\", GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=0)),\n",
    "    ])\n",
    "    return pipeline_base\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "PipelineClf2ExplainClusters()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d08",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["Fit the classifier to the training data"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pipeline_clf_cluster = PipelineClf2ExplainClusters()\n",
    "pipeline_clf_cluster.fit(X_train, y_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Evaluate classifier performance on Train and Test Sets"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d11",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report\n",
    "\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_train, pipeline_clf_cluster.predict(X_train)))\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, pipeline_clf_cluster.predict(X_test)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d12",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Assess the most important Features that define a cluster"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# after data cleaning and feature engineering, the feature space changes\n",
    "# how many data cleaning and feature engineering steps does your pipeline have?\n",
    "data_cleaning_feat_eng_steps = 2\n",
    "columns_after_data_cleaning_feat_eng = (\n",
    "    Pipeline(pipeline_clf_cluster.steps[:data_cleaning_feat_eng_steps])\n",
    "    .transform(X_train)\n",
    "    .columns\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "best_features = columns_after_data_cleaning_feat_eng[\n",
    "    pipeline_clf_cluster['feat_selection'].get_support()].to_list()\n",
    "\n",
    "# create DataFrame to display feature importance\n",
    "df_feature_importance = (\n",
    "    pd.DataFrame(data={\n",
    "        'Feature': columns_after_data_cleaning_feat_eng[\n",
    "            pipeline_clf_cluster['feat_selection'].get_support()],\n",
    "        'Importance': pipeline_clf_cluster['model'].feature_importances_})\n",
    "    .sort_values(by='Importance', ascending=False)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# reassign best features in importance order\n",
    "best_features = df_feature_importance['Feature'].to_list()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Most important features statement and plot\n",
    "print(f\"* These are the {len(best_features)} most important features in \"\n",
    "      f\"descending order. The model was trained on them: \\n{best_features} \\n\")\n",
    "df_feature_importance.plot(kind='bar', x='Feature', y='Importance')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-d14",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["We will store the `best_features` to use at a later stage."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-d15",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "best_features_pipeline_all_variables = best_features\n",
    "best_features_pipeline_all_variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-e01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Cluster Analysis"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-e02",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Load function that plots a table with description for all Clusters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-e03",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def DescriptionAllClusters(df, decimal_points=3):\n",
    "\n",
    "    DescriptionAllClusters = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "        columns=df.drop(['Clusters'], axis=1).columns)\n",
    "    for cluster in df.sort_values(by='Clusters')['Clusters'].unique():\n",
    "\n",
    "        EDA_ClusterSubset = df.query(\n",
    "            f\"Clusters == {cluster}\").drop(['Clusters'], axis=1)\n",
    "        ClusterDescription = Clusters_IndividualDescription(\n",
    "            EDA_ClusterSubset, cluster, decimal_points)\n",
    "        DescriptionAllClusters = pd.concat(\n",
    "            [ClusterDescription, DescriptionAllClusters])\n",
    "\n",
    "    DescriptionAllClusters.set_index(['Cluster'], inplace=True)\n",
    "    return DescriptionAllClusters\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def Clusters_IndividualDescription(EDA_Cluster, cluster, decimal_points):\n",
    "\n",
    "    ClustersDescription = pd.DataFrame(columns=EDA_Cluster.columns)\n",
    "    for col in EDA_Cluster.columns:\n",
    "\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            if EDA_Cluster[col].dtypes == 'object':\n",
    "\n",
    "                top_frequencies = (\n",
    "                    EDA_Cluster.dropna(subset=[col])[[col]]\n",
    "                    .value_counts(normalize=True)\n",
    "                    .nlargest(n=3)\n",
    "                )\n",
    "                Description = ''\n",
    "                for x in range(len(top_frequencies)):\n",
    "                    freq = top_frequencies.iloc[x]\n",
    "                    category = top_frequencies.index[x][0]\n",
    "                    CategoryPercentage = int(round(freq * 100, 0))\n",
    "                    statement = f\"'{category}': {CategoryPercentage}% , \"\n",
    "                    Description = Description + statement\n",
    "                ClustersDescription.at[0, col] = Description[:-2]\n",
    "\n",
    "            elif EDA_Cluster[col].dtypes in ['float64', 'int64', 'float', 'int']:\n",
    "                DescStats = EDA_Cluster.dropna(subset=[col])[[col]].describe()\n",
    "                Q1 = round(DescStats.iloc[4, 0], decimal_points)\n",
    "                Q3 = round(DescStats.iloc[6, 0], decimal_points)\n",
    "                Description = f\"{Q1} -- {Q3}\"\n",
    "                ClustersDescription.at[0, col] = Description\n",
    "\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            ClustersDescription.at[0, col] = 'Not available'\n",
    "            print(\n",
    "                f\"** Error Exception: {e} - cluster {cluster}, variable {col}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    ClustersDescription['Cluster'] = str(cluster)\n",
    "    return ClustersDescription"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-e04",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Load a custom function to plot cluster distribution per Variable (absolute and relative levels)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-e05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import plotly.express as px\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def cluster_distribution_per_variable(df, target):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    The data should have 2 variables: the cluster predictions and\n",
    "    the variable you want to analyse. We use plotly express to create 2 plots:\n",
    "    Cluster distribution across the target.\n",
    "    Relative presence of the target level in each cluster.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    df_bar_plot = df.groupby(['Clusters', target]).size().reset_index(name='Count')\n",
    "    df_bar_plot.columns = ['Clusters', target, 'Count']\n",
    "    df_bar_plot[target] = df_bar_plot[target].astype('object')\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Clusters distribution across {target} levels\")\n",
    "    fig = px.bar(df_bar_plot, x='Clusters', y='Count',\n",
    "                 color=target, width=800, height=500)\n",
    "    fig.update_layout(xaxis=dict(tickmode='array',\n",
    "                      tickvals=df['Clusters'].unique()))\n",
    "    fig.show(renderer='jupyterlab')\n",
    "\n",
    "    df_relative = (\n",
    "        df\n",
    "        .groupby([\"Clusters\", target])\n",
    "        .size()\n",
    "        .unstack(fill_value=0)\n",
    "        .apply(lambda x: 100 * x / x.sum(), axis=1)\n",
    "        .stack()\n",
    "        .reset_index(name='Relative Percentage (%)')\n",
    "        .sort_values(by=['Clusters', target])\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"Relative Percentage (%) of {target} in each cluster\")\n",
    "    fig = px.line(df_relative, x='Clusters', y='Relative Percentage (%)',\n",
    "                  color=target, width=800, height=500)\n",
    "    fig.update_layout(xaxis=dict(tickmode='array',\n",
    "                      tickvals=df['Clusters'].unique()))\n",
    "    fig.update_traces(mode='markers+lines')\n",
    "    fig.show(renderer='jupyterlab')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-e06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
