   "id": "cell-g08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X['Clusters'] = pipeline_cluster['model'].labels_\n",
    "print(X.shape)\n",
    "X.head(3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-g09",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(f\"* Clusters frequencies \\n{\n",
    "    X['Clusters'].value_counts(normalize=True).to_frame().round(2)} \\n\\n\")\n",
    "X['Clusters'].value_counts().sort_values().plot(kind='bar')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-g10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## Compare current cluster predictions to previous cluster predictions"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-g11",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We just fitted a new cluster pipeline and want to compare if its predictions are "equivalent" to the previous cluster.\n",
    "\n",
    "These are the predictions from the previous cluster pipeline — trained with all variables:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-g12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cluster_predictions_with_all_variables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cell-g13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And these are the predictions from the current cluster pipeline (trained with the best features):"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
